title: Matchsafe, "Fish with Glass Eye", 1908–09
markings: 925, London import mark both stamped on head, ETB (unidentified retailer's mark?), London import mark, 925, date letter "n" stamped on gill. 930 stamped on tail.
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
creditline: Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener
description: In the shape of a fish with incised decoration of scales, fins, gills and two red glass eyes. Head flips open, hinged on top. Link attached at top. Scales likely intended as striker.

tombstone.epitaph:
Matchsafe, "Fish with Glass Eye", 1908–09.
1908–09. Silver. Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener. 1982-23-1116.
